{Box}is known throughout the length and breadth of the country (in the railway enthusiasts world!) for the{Box {Tunnel. { Isambard Kingdom Brunel}built the {Great Western Railway}during the 1830's and the early forties.{Box {Tunnel}was completed in 1841, after taking hundreds of "navvies" months to cut through the hillside.It is said that on{Brunels}birthday, April 9th, if you stand at the western end of the Tunnel,at dawn you can see the sun rise.
